Package utils.exceptions

package utils.exceptions
The utils.exceptions package contains the exceptions that can be thrown by the application.
  • Related Packages
    Package
    Description
    utils
    The utils package contains utility classes, including exceptions, checks, and other helper classes.
  • Exceptions
    Class
    Description
    AccountNotFoundException
    The AccountNotFoundException class is a custom exception that is thrown when an account is not found.
    PageBackException
    The PageBackException class is a custom exception that is thrown when a user attempts to navigate back from a UI page where it is not allowed.
    PasswordIncorrectException
    The PasswordIncorrectException is thrown when the provided password is incorrect.
    PasswordMismatchException
    The PasswordMismatchException is thrown when the provided passwords do not match.
    PasswordValidationException
    The PasswordValidationException is thrown when the provided password does not meet the requirements.
    TooFewManagersException
    The TooFewManagersException is thrown when there are too few managers in a branch.
    TooManyManagersException
    The TooManyManagersException is thrown when there are too many managers in a branch.
